cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a method to achieve a reliable confidence score for neural network classifiers, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on deep learning and proposes a method based on the data embedding derived from the penultimate layer of the network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions Bayesian models, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses novelty detection, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
